        "content": {
          "subject": "math",
          "topic": "proof_and_logic",
          "subtopic": null,
          "archetype": null,
          "difficulty": 4,
          "requires_diagram": false,
          "requires_calculation": true
        },
        "prompt": {
          "stem": "Consider the following attempt to prove this true theorem:\\n\\n*Theorem:* $a^3 + b^3 = c^3$ has no solutions with $a$, $b$ and $c$ positive integers.\\n\\n*Attempted proof:*\\nSuppose that there are positive integers $a$, $b$ and $c$ such that $a^3 + b^3 = c^3$.\\n\\nI\\tWe have $a^3 = c^3 - b^3$.\\n\\nII\\tHence $a^3 = (c-b)(c^2 + cb + b^2)$.\\n\\nIII\\tIt follows that $a = c-b$ and $a^2 = c^2 + cb + b^2$, since $a \\leq a^2$ and $c-b \\leq c^2 + cb + b^2$.\\n\\nIV\\tEliminating $a$, we have $(c-b)^2 = c^2 + cb + b^2$.\\n\\nV\\tMultiplying out, we have $c^2 - 2cb + b^2 = c^2 + cb + b^2$.\\n\\nVI\\tHence $3cb = 0$ so one of $b$ and $c$ is zero.\\n\\nBut this is a contradiction to the original assumption that all of $a$, $b$ and $c$ are positive. It follows that the equation has no solutions.\\n\\nComment on this proof by choosing one of the following options:",
          "options": [
            {
              "label": "A",
              "text": "The proof is correct"
            },
            {
              "label": "B",
              "text": "The proof is incorrect and the first mistake occurs on line I."
            },
            {
              "label": "C",
              "text": "The proof is incorrect and the first mistake occurs on line II."
            },
            {
              "label": "D",
              "text": "The proof is incorrect and the first mistake occurs on line III."
            },
            {
              "label": "E",
              "text": "The proof is incorrect and the first mistake occurs on line IV."
            },
            {
              "label": "F",
              "text": "The proof is incorrect and the first mistake occurs on line V."
            },
            {
              "label": "G",
              "text": "The proof is incorrect and the first mistake occurs on line VI."
            }
          ],
          "figures": []
        },
